"signal_description": "The SIGNAL query is selecting several columns from the 'defaultview-225' table. It renames 'Inv. Company Code' to 'Company Code', 'Inv. Company Code Text' to 'Company Code Name', 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Number' to 'Vendor Number', and 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Name' to 'Vendor Name'. It also creates a new column 'Immediate PT behaviour' based on the values of 'Last PO Vendor Master Cash Discount Days 1', 'Last PO Cash Discount Days 1', and 'Last Inv. Item Cash Discount Days 1'. If 'Last PO Vendor Master Cash Discount Days 1' equals 0, it assigns 'Immediate PT in Master Data'. If 'Last PO Cash Discount Days 1' equals 0, it assigns 'Immediate PT on PO'. If 'Last PO Cash Discount Days 1' is not 0 and 'Last Inv. Item Cash Discount Days 1' equals 0, it assigns 'Immediate PT on Invoice but not on PO'. If 'Last Inv. Item Cash Discount Days 1' is not 0 and 'Last PO Cash Discount Days 1' equals 0, it assigns 'Immediate PT on PO but not on Invoice'. In all other cases, it assigns 'ok'. The query also counts the number of case_id's and renames it to 'Number of Invoices'. It sums up the 'Inv. Converted USD Amount' and renames it to 'Invoice Amounts'. The results are grouped by the first five selected columns and ordered by the third column in descending order."
